bresize2fs - backward resize2fs

This program was created to optimize/simplify moving the beginning of ext
filesystems while changing their size.

The usual (non-optimized) way of doing this is to:
 - for extending:
1) move the filesystem left on the disk layout
2) call resize2fs
 - for shrinking:
1) call resize2fs
2) move the filesystem right on the disk layout

As it can be seen, a lot of data (the whole filesystem) must be copied. This
process consumes a lot of time and wears out the disk.

That's what this program was created for. It will do the same operations but
using the optimized way that doesn't require copying of all of the data. If
it isn't possible, the program will suggest the changes in the partition
layout to allow the optimized way to function.

Currently, the program is not yet ready to use. It requires refactoring and
implementing of the core logic (see "todo!"s in the code).
